. Why CSS? Inline vs. Internal vs. External
Inline Style:
<h2 style="color: red;">Upcoming Events</h2>

 Internal Style:
<head>
  <style>
    body {
      background-color: #f0f0f0;
    }
  </style>
</head>

External Style:
<link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">

In styles.css:
/* Header styles */
#welcomeBanner {
  background-color: #007BFF;
  color: white;
  padding: 10px;
  text-align: center;
}

2. CSS Syntax and Comments
/* Reset default padding and margin */
* {
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
  box-sizing: border-box;
}

/* Style for main CTA button */
.cta-button {
  background-color: #007BFF;
  color: white;
  padding: 10px 20px;
  border-radius: 5px;
  font-weight: bold;
}

3. Selectors Playground
/* Universal selector */
* {
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
}

/* Element selector */
h2 {
  font-size: 24px;
  margin-bottom: 10px;
}

/* ID selector */
#mainHeader {
  background-color: #333;
  color: white;
}

/* Class selector */
.eventCard {
  padding: 20px;
  border: 1px solid #ccc;
  margin: 15px;
}

/* Grouping selector */
h3, p {
  color: #333;
  font-family: sans-serif;
}

4. Color & Background Styling
/* Use HEX and RGBA */
body {
  background-color: #ffffff;
  color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8);
  background-image: url('city.jpg');
  background-size: cover;
  background-repeat: no-repeat;
}

/* Gradient header */
section h2 {
  background: linear-gradient(to right, #007BFF, #00BCD4);
  color: white;
  padding: 10px;
}

 5. Typography: Fonts and Text
In <head>:
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Roboto&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

In styles.css:
body {
  font-family: 'Roboto', sans-serif;
  line-height: 1.6;
}

/* Description section */
.description {
  text-align: justify;
  text-transform: capitalize;
  letter-spacing: 0.5px;
}

6. Link and List Styling
nav a:link {
  color: #007BFF;
}

nav a:hover {
  color: #0056b3;
}

nav a:active {
  color: red;
}

nav a:visited {
  color: purple;
}

nav ul {
  list-style-type: none;
  padding: 0;
  margin: 0;
}

nav li {
  margin-right: 20px;
  display: inline;
}

7. Table Styling
table {
  width: 100%;
  border-collapse: collapse;
}

th, td {
  padding: 10px;
  border: 1px solid #ddd;
  text-align: center;
}

tr:nth-child(even) {
  background-color: #f2f2f2;
}

 8. Box Model & Layout Control
.eventCard {
  margin: 20px;
  padding: 15px;
  border: 1px solid #ccc;
  outline: 2px dashed #888;
}

.hidden {
  visibility: hidden;
}

.removed {
  display: none;
}

 9. Multiple Columns in Text
<section class="news">
  <h2>Community Bulletin</h2>
  <div class="article">
    <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Curabitur...</p>
  </div>
</section>

10. Responsive Web Design with Media Queries
@media screen and (max-width: 768px) {
  nav a {
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }

  img {
    width: 100%;
  }

  body {
    font-size: 14px;
  }

  .eventCard {
    width: 100%;
  }
}

11. Debug and Test with DevTools and VS Code
 Use device toolbar (Ctrl+Shift+M in DevTools) to test mobile/tablet/desktop views.

 Use "Elements" tab to try CSS changes live.

 Console tab helps debug JS issues.

 Network tab to confirm styles.css is loading
